From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 13 Nov 2024 15:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Set skb->dev for kernels < 3.13 in HCI receive path

For kernel versions older than 3.13, hci_recv_frame() expects skb->dev
to be set to the HCI device structure. Without this, the kernel cannot
route the received packets to the correct HCI device.

This is critical for proper HCI operation on kernel 3.10 (used by Thingino).

Signed-off-by: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 smac/bdev.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/smac/bdev.c b/smac/bdev.c
index 1234567..89abcdef 100644
--- a/smac/bdev.c
+++ b/smac/bdev.c
@@ -96,6 +96,9 @@ int ssv_ble_hci_rx_packet(u8 *rx_packet, u32 rx_len)
 #if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(3,13,0)
     hci_recv_frame(ssv_hdev,bskb);
 #else
+    /* For older kernels, must set skb->dev to the HCI device */
+    bskb->dev = (void *)ssv_hdev;
+
     hci_recv_frame(bskb);
 #endif
 #endif
--
2.34.1
